        "title": "security: add Security Matrix runtime-fact audit model",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a Security Matrix runtime-fact evaluator.\n- Models actor, influence source, tool capability, approval state, and operator policy as separate inputs.\n- Adds default policy data, a deterministic evaluator, tool capability resolution, an audit-event object builder, tests, and documentation.\n- Adds a small before-tool-call fact adapter so future runtime wiring can build the same audit event shape from explicit boundary facts without changing execution behavior.\n- Hardens custom policy parsing so malformed decisions cannot weaken the default policy.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis PR remains non-enforcing and observe-only.\n\nIt does not block tool calls, require confirmation at runtime, emit runtime diagnostic events, change UI, change plugin behavior, or alter runtime tool execution. The before-tool-call adapter only builds an audit event object and exposes an explicit opt-in config predicate for future wiring.\n\n## Validation\n\nValidated locally at PR head `d192028ab6cd7f962a7007f0f94c77d6b8b8e4aa`.\n\nCommands run:\n\n```bash\npnpm test src/security/security-matrix/evaluate.test.ts src/agents/security-matrix-before-call.test.ts\npnpm changed:lanes --base upstream/main --json\npnpm exec oxlint src/security/security-matrix/ src/agents/security-matrix-before-call.test.ts\nnode scripts/format-docs.mjs --check docs/security/security-matrix.md\ngit diff --check upstream/main...HEAD\n```\n\nResults:\n\n- Focused tests passed: `src/security/security-matrix/evaluate.test.ts` and `src/agents/security-matrix-before-call.test.ts`\n- `Test Files 2 passed (2)`\n- `Tests 28 passed (28)`\n- changed-lanes reported `core=true`, `coreTests=true`, `docs=true`, `tooling=true`\n- changed-lanes reported `extensions=false`, `extensionTests=false`, `apps=false`, `liveDockerTooling=false`, `releaseMetadata=false`, `all=false`\n- oxlint completed with no reported errors\n- docs formatting reported `Docs formatting clean (663 files).`\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD` reported no whitespace errors\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Security Matrix runtime-fact evaluation now produces deterministic audit decisions from actor, influence source, capability, approval state, and operator policy. The before-tool-call adapter builds the same audit-event shape from explicit boundary facts without emitting, blocking, or mutating execution. Malformed custom policy decisions are ignored instead of being treated as policy output.\n- Real environment tested: Local Linux checkout at `~/projects/openclaw`, branch `security/matrix-audit-model`, PR head `d192028ab6cd7f962a7007f0f94c77d6b8b8e4aa`, Node v24.15.0 via the repository pnpm environment.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. Ran focused tests through the repository `pnpm test` wrapper.\n  2. Ran changed-lane detection, targeted oxlint, docs formatting, and whitespace checks.\n  3. Added regression coverage for malformed custom policy decisions shaped as both an object and a string.\n- Evidence after fix:\n\n```text\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  28 passed (28)\nDocs formatting clean (663 files).\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The evaluator keeps the default `web_fetch` + `exec` block decision when custom policy data contains invalid decision values such as `permit`, even when `allowPolicyWeakening` is enabled. Valid policy decisions still resolve through the existing deterministic rule path.\n- What was not tested: Runtime hook emission, runtime enforcement, strict config schema adoption, CLI display, plugin UI, and live tool execution are intentionally not changed by this PR.",
